    <article>
      <h1>The Epic of SERPheus: A Literary Pilgrimage through SEO</h1>
      <p><em>—By Manish Yadav (Tatva Tech Digital)</em></p>

      <section>
        <h2>🪶 Invocation: The Muse of Meta</h2>
        <p>O Muse of Tags, of Title’s flame,<br>
        Who sings in code and marketer’s name,<br>
        In Eliot’s waste or Milton’s pyre,<br>
        Guide my hand with crawler’s fire.</p>

        <p>For what is SEO, if not verse reborn,<br>
        A structured sonnet, not forlorn?<br>
        Like sonnets shaped by meter’s rule,<br>
        My schema lives by indexing school.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>✨ Canto I — Of Keywords, Cannons, and Code</h2>
        <p>In Chaucer’s tongue and Shakespeare’s lines,<br>
        I etch my page in bold designs.<br>
        Yet no mere bardic song I weave—<br>
        But <strong>keyword clusters</strong> well retrieved.</p>

        <p>Ah! Keywords — the monads of intent,<br>
        Like Wordsworth’s joy in rustic scent.<br>
        Long-tail or head, they shape the tale,<br>
        As Joyce rewrote the epic scale.</p>

        <p><strong>Meta title</strong>, H1 bold,<br>
        With <strong>LSI</strong> in stories told.<br>
        In Coleridge’s dream and Derrida’s sign,<br>
        The <strong>searcher’s query</strong> becomes mine.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>⚙️ Canto II — Of Technical Thrones and Gothic Crawl</h2>
        <p><strong>Oh Googlebot</strong>, thy Gothic crawl,<br>
        Thy phantom steps through server hall.<br>
        My robots.txt like haunted doors,<br>
        Directs thy gaze through silent floors.</p>

        <p><strong>Canonical tags</strong> — my doppelgänger’s cure,<br>
        To fix the page that looks unsure.<br>
        No 404 shall waste this land,<br>
        For Eliot’s ruin, I shall withstand.</p>

        <p><strong>Page speed</strong>, the Shelleyan breath of light,<br>
        Lighthouse tests run through the night.<br>
        Minified JS, lazy-load art,<br>
        Compression plays the poet’s part.</p>

        <p><strong>Mobile-first</strong>—the postmodern verse,<br>
        Responsive grids in CSS rehearse.<br>
        With Foucault’s panopticon I see,<br>
        Analytics track thy steps for me.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>🔗 Canto III — Of Links, Lords, and Postcolonial Rank</h2>
        <p>Now speaks the ghost of link divine—<br>
        A backlink’s power, page’s spine.<br>
        Like Byron’s fame from printed tongue,<br>
        A link from Moz is richly sung.</p>

        <p><strong>Internal links</strong>, the Austen dance,<br>
        From post to post, in themed romance.<br>
        <strong>Anchor text</strong>, that whispered clue,<br>
        A Shakespeare quote in digital hue.</p>

        <p>No cloaked disguise nor PBN<br>
        Shall stain my site with black-hat sin.<br>
        Like Swift, I satire tricks in prose—<br>
        For <strong>white-hat ethics</strong> bloom and grow.</p>

        <p><strong>Local SEO</strong>, my regional soul,<br>
        Like Tagore’s tongue, it makes me whole.<br>
        NAP consistent, map well placed,<br>
        In search proximity, I'm graced.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>🧠 Canto IV — Of Semantics, Structure, and AI’s Eye</h2>
        <p>Now enters Google's sacred core—<br>
        A <strong>BERT-born AI</strong>, folklore.<br>
        Context reigns, no fluff survives,<br>
        The poem ranks by <strong>searcher’s lives</strong>.</p>

        <p><strong>Entity-based SEO</strong>, I chant,<br>
        Like Joyce’s stream, both dense and slant.<br>
        From context, history, to intent,<br>
        Each paragraph is <strong>meaning-bent</strong>.</p>

        <p><strong>Structured data</strong>, JSON’s delight,<br>
        Like stage direction in Wilde’s light.<br>
        Breadcrumbs, ratings, FAQ flair—<br>
        I markup dreams with search-aware care.</p>

        <p><strong>EEAT</strong>, the critic’s voice returns,<br>
        With <strong>experience</strong>, the wisdom burns.<br>
        Authority from niche-born deeds,<br>
        And trust from real-world user needs.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>🌌 Epilogue — SERPheus Ascends</h2>
        <p>Thus SERPheus walked the SEO shore,<br>
        From content cave to backlink door.<br>
        With Plato’s forms and Google’s core,<br>
        He wrote in light what came before.</p>

        <p>O reader, crawl this epic still,<br>
        Like Woolf through rooms that thought could fill.<br>
        And if thy bounce be high or rank be low,<br>
        Rewrite thy path—<strong>become SEO</strong>.</p>
      </section>

